The paper deals with compressive sensing and structured sparsity, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also proposes new algorithms for solving the recovery problem, which involves optimization and computational complexity, making it relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
